			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="1">
				The word that came to Jeremiah from the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				:
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24030002">
			</marker>
			<verse num="2">
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Thus says the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				, the God of Israel: 
				<crossref let="e" cid="c24030002.1">
				</crossref>
				Write in a book all the words that I have spoken to you.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v24030003">
			</marker>
			<verse num="3">
				<crossref let="f" cid="c24030003.1">
				</crossref>
				For behold, days are coming, declares the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				, 
				<crossref let="g" cid="c24030003.2">
				</crossref>
				when I will restore 
				<crossref let="h" cid="c24030003.3">
				</crossref>
				the fortunes of my people, 
				<crossref let="i" cid="c24030003.4">
				</crossref>
				Israel and Judah, says the 
				<span class="divine-name">
					Lord
				</span>
				, 
				<crossref let="j" cid="c24030003.5">
				</crossref>
				and I will bring them back to the land that I gave to their fathers, and they shall take possession of it.
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
